<doc id="468600" wikidata="Q10724146" url="?curid=468600" title="Zamunda">
<text>Zamunda is a genus of crickets in the subfamily Podoscirtinae and tribe Aphonoidini. Species have been found in southern China and peninsular Malaysia (known distribution may be incomplete).

== Species ==
&quot;Zamunda&quot; includes the following species:
* &quot;Zamunda fuscirostris&quot; (Chopard, 1969) – type species (as &quot;Aphonoides fuscirostris&quot; Chopard)
* &quot;Zamunda humeralis&quot; Gorochov, 2007

== Fictitious Use ==
&quot;Zamunda&quot; is the name of the African nation where Eddie Murphy&#x27;s character, crown prince Akeem Joffer, is from in the 1988 film Coming to America. There is no such nation in Africa.

== References ==
